# Notes Sharing App
Stack: Go (Fiber, GORM, JWT) + PostgreSQL + Next.js

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£ How to run backend
    cd backend
    go run main.go

    Stop backend: tekan Ctrl + C

# 2Ô∏è‚É£ How to run database (PostgreSQL)
    Start all services in detached mode:
        docker-compose up -d

    Stop all services:
        docker-compose down
    
    Rebuild & refresh containers (useful after changes):
        docker-compose down
        docker-compose up --build
    
    Access PostgreSQL inside container:
        docker exec -it notesdb psql -U postgres -d notesdb

    List databases:
        \l
    
    Connect to a specific database:
        \c notesdb

    List tables:
        \dt

    View table content:
        SELECT * FROM <table_name>;

    Exit psql:
        \q
    
# 3Ô∏è‚É£ How to run frontend
        cd frontend
        npm install
        npm run dev
    
    Stop frontend: tekan Ctrl + C

    Build & run for production:
        npm run build
        npm run start

# 4Ô∏è‚É£ Viewing logs (live)
    Backend logs:
        docker-compose logs -f backend
    
    Frontend logs:
        docker-compose logs -f frontend
    
    Database logs:
        docker-compose logs -f postgres

üí° Tip: Add --tail 100 to see 100 on behind.

# 5Ô∏è‚É£ Additional tips
    Check ports in use:
        netstat -ano | findstr :<port_number>
    
    Kill a process by PID (Windows):
        taskkill /PID <PID> /F
    
    List Docker containers:
        docker ps -a
    
    Remove unused Docker containers/images:
        docker system prune